column3: Required field - "Contact Type" - 211 Call: Select when caller is looking for information or resources for self, family member, family, friend, client, or own organization. Admin Call: Select when Professional is calling as a representative of their organization with administrative questions about their relationship with 2-1-1. Contract: Slect if the call is related to a specific call center contract. Escape Call: Select if this is a test call or if the client hung up before you could ascertain any information.
column4: Should remove escape calls from the data - if there are blank values here there amy have been an error in a previous project form. Come to us for any clarification if something looks wonky.

column3:
Only appears is Admin is selected in "ContactType2" - Resource: Select if organization calls to update their resource listing, inquire about being listed in database or publication, or to talk with
resource manager about other database concern. Material Request: Select if agency calls to restock promotional or resource materials for general use in their organization. Do not use if agency is calling on behalf of specific client and requests a copy of a resource directory. If information is for a specific client, it would be considered a 2-1-1 Call. Other: Any other administrative call from a professional representative of
an organization.
column4: None

column3:
"Calling on behalf of" Self: Select if no other household members are indicated OR if request only directly benefits the caller as an individual. Friend: Select if caller is calling on behalf of someone they know but are not related to and person in need is not in the same household. Family member:Select if person in need is related to the caller but does not live in same household OR if service only directly benefits a single member of the household who is not the caller. Family: Select if other household members are indicated AND request will benefit
multiple
column4: None

column3: "Who is calling" - Client: Select if professional is calling for resources for a client, parishioner, employee, etc. Not for general benefit of their organization. Organization: Select if professional is calling for resources or materials for the general use/benefit of organization or for reference (no particular client indicated)
column4: None

column3: "what type of professional" - Agency: Select if professional is calling for their own organization or for a client who receives services. Clergy: Select when caller is church/synagogue/mosque/faith community staff or representative. Employer: Select if professional is calling for an employee. Agencies can be marked as employers if they are calling for an employee of the agency. Law Enforcement :Select if caller is representative of police, emergency medical personnel, fire department. Other: Select if professional is calling but does not fit any above definitions
column4: None

column3: Information Only: Select when giving information in response to specific inquiries, like a program’s phone number, address, hours, etc. (See 2019 AIRS I&R Training Manual). Select Information Only if an unmet need is recorded and no other referrals were given. If a call is mental health-related with no referral, log it as Information Only and save a referral to your center. Information & Referral: Select when assessment is performed and referrals are given. Caller may be aware of problem in a general way, but need assistance to define specific needs and identify sources of help. (See 2019 AIRS I&R Training Manual). Crisis: Select when performing crisis intervention to ensure safety of caller or others. Can include medical or psychiatric emergency, domestic violence, child or vulnerable adult abuse/neglect, or other forms of distress. Often used when referrals or transfers are made to crisis centers, law enforcement, medical or fire emergency personnel. (See 2019 AIRS I&R Training Manual: Roles of an I&R). No Referral Given: Select when no referrals, OODs, or unmet needs are recorded
column4: None

column3: Only viewable if "211CallType" equals "No Referral Given" - Select appropriate Reason for No Referral. Call Terminated: Select when call disconnects before any referral information can be given. If need was expressed and was a definite unmet need, record the unmet need and mark Information Only. If you know the need the caller is calling about, log with Refer To Needs Only and choose correct Taxonomy term. Prank Call: Select for any prank calls. Wrong Number: Select when caller called 2-1-1 by mistake and no other numbers are provided by I&R Specialist. If specialist provides caller with the correct contact information for the number they were originally trying to reach, record referral and mark Information Only
